{
  "texts": [
    "It is noteworthy that our study represents the first reported demonstration in the field of SRMs, utilizing a purely self-rectifying memristor-based passive crossbar array for hardware implementations of NN applications.",
    "While the energy efficiency of the proposed CA is currently lower than ref.",
    "36,56., we anticipate that higher efficiency can be achieved by increasing the array density.",
    "Furthermore, we compare the energy efficiency of our hardware accelerator with traditional microelectronic chips such as GPUs, FPGAs, and ASICs in Table 2.",
    "The results of the comparison show that our hardware accelerator achieves relatively high energy efficiency due to significantly lower power consumption compared to traditional microelectronic chips."
  ]
}